      <hedline>
        <hl1>JetBlue Airways Shifts Assignment</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Allison Fass</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Fass, Allison</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>JetBlue Airways dismisses its ad agency, Merkley Newman Harty, and shifts its account to Arnold Communications; billings estimated at $10 million (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>JetBlue Airways, a start-up airline based in Queens, has dismissed its agency of a year and a half, Merkley Newman Harty in New York, and shifted its account to Arnold Communications in Boston. Billings were estimated at $10 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>JetBlue Airways, a start-up airline based in Queens, has dismissed its agency of a year and a half, Merkley Newman Harty in New York, and shifted its account to Arnold Communications in Boston. Billings were estimated at $10 million.</p>
        <p>Kel Kelly, who recently joined JetBlue as executive vice president for marketing and sales, attributed the agency change to her positive experiences working with Arnold in the past. Arnold is part of Snyder Communications, which is being acquired by Havas Advertising. Merkley Newman is part of the Omnicom Group.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
